        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is a 17-year-old girl from the Czech Republic who arrives with a quiet, slowed demeanor and limited eye contact. Over the last few weeks she has had a persistently depressed mood lasting at least 2 weeks, and she describes feeling mentally tired, with poor motivation and difficulty concentrating at school; these features fit a depressive episode with impaired neurovegetative functioning, psychomotor activity, and cognition [PMID:36156484, MEDDIALOG:F32.9:0]. She also reports intermittent anxiety alongside the depression [MEDDIALOG:F32.9:0].\n\nShe is in secondary school and used to enjoy drawing and spending time with two close friends after classes, but recently she has withdrawn and spends more time alone in her room. Her mother says she seems slower getting ready in the morning and no longer shows much interest in hobbies. She has not been working a job and lives with her parents, which is a clinically plausible adolescent home setting.\n\nWhen speaking, {patientName} admits that dark thoughts have been present, including passive thoughts that life is not worth much, which is concerning because depressive episodes can include suicidal thoughts [PMID:36156484]. She denies hearing voices or having fixed false beliefs, and there is no history suggesting psychotic symptoms at present; severe depression can have psychotic symptoms, but this is not evident in her current presentation [MEDDIALOG:F32.9:2].\n\nHer family describes her as previously reliable and social, but now more tearful and isolated. They brought her in because the low mood has started to affect attendance, homework completion, and family interaction. There is no sign of intoxication, and the history does not suggest substance use as the main driver of symptoms, which is clinically plausible for this scenario."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:24df1dae-a94a-41b0-b74b-6749eebd3424",
